{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":19898,"name":"Samson","username":"qwertysam","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/qwertysam/{size}/758_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-05T17:34:31.460Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHello! So my question is quite simple to ask (perhaps more difficult to answer); is it possible to select the type of filtering that applies to my StaticSprite2D objects?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor example, this is what I’ve been working on:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/eacf74b9b68a641575bf3993f98b190c49b1a701.png\" title=\"bzR2Gwq.png\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/eacf74b9b68a641575bf3993f98b190c49b1a701.png\" width=\"690\" height=\"248\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/1X/eacf74b9b68a641575bf3993f98b190c49b1a701_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003ebzR2Gwq.png\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e697×251 1.1 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe ship looks great. What I want is a 23 pixel high image that I can scale up by 4 in the code to achieve a 92 pixel high result on the screen. When I do that, this is the result that I get:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/91260bc0b8a28e66f1bc000824c4a543e375875b.png\" alt=\"Screenshot from 2017-08-05 13-24-13\" width=\"117\" height=\"121\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePretty gross, right? It appears to be using a Linear or Cubic scaling algorithm, which is not what I want. I would like to tell it to use a Nearest Neighbour scaling algorithm so that I can get those crisp pixels that will compliment the art. After about a week of searching, the documentation left me struck with no leads.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMy current workaround is to scale the image before-hand and load up a much larger image to be rendered. It’s quite extraneous and not particularly fun or optimised for loading.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIs there any proper or better solution that I’m missing?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThanks!\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-05-23T13:20:01.891Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":33,"reads":42,"readers_count":41,"score":175.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":3422,"topic_slug":"sprite-texture-nearest-neighbour-filtering","display_username":"Samson","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/1X/eacf74b9b68a641575bf3993f98b190c49b1a701.png","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"eacf74b9b68a641575bf3993f98b190c49b1a701.png","clicks":0}],"read":true,"user_title":null,"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":775,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":"downloaded local copies of images","can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false},{"id":19899,"name":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","username":"Modanung","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/{size}/3290_2.png","created_at":"2017-08-05T18:26:01.028Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eTry this:\u003cbr\u003e\n\u003caside class=\"onebox whitelistedgeneric\"\u003e\n  \u003cheader class=\"source\"\u003e\n      \u003cimg src=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/images/default-favicon.ico\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\"\u003e\n      \u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/tile-maps-seeing-neighbor-tiles/2931/2?u=modanung\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eUrho3D\u003c/a\u003e\n  \u003c/header\u003e\n  \u003carticle class=\"onebox-body\"\u003e\n    \u003cimg src=\"https://sjc6.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/modanung/200/1123_1.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\"\u003e\n\n\u003ch3\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://discourse.urho3d.io/t/tile-maps-seeing-neighbor-tiles/2931/2?u=modanung\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003eTile maps: Seeing neighbor tiles\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eFrom the documentation on Urho2D:       You need to create an XML file in the same folder as the texture, with the same name (but ending in xml) containing:           \u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n  \u003c/article\u003e\n  \u003cdiv class=\"onebox-metadata\"\u003e\n    \n    \n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"clear: both\"\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/aside\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnd welcome to the forums! \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=5\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2017-08-08T16:51:50.248Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":40,"readers_count":39,"score":43.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":3422,"topic_slug":"sprite-texture-nearest-neighbour-filtering","display_username":"魔大农 𝞍𝞎𝝳 現招蜍","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version